                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.944,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has our opinion this morning in case 12-1497, Kellogg Brown \u0026 Root v. Carter."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.944,
                        "stop": 156.792,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15068,
                            "name": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/samuel_alito_jr",
                            "last_name": "Alito",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2712,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1138687200,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2712"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32684,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 44799,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/samuel_a_alito_jr_1.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 3531,
                            "identifier": "samuel_alito_jr"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.944,
                                "stop": 17.645,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In this case we decide two questions concerning laws that relate to frauds committed against the federal government during wartime."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.645,
                                "stop": 20.644,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "One of these laws is the False Claims Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.644,
                                "stop": 27.593,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Under that act the government can sue those who present false or fraudulent claims for payment to the government."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 27.593,
                                "stop": 32.489,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Individuals can also bring qui tam actions on the government\u0027s behalf."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 32.489,
                                "stop": 48.03,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The other law is the Wartime Suspension of Limitations Act and as the name of the act suggests what this does is to suspend the Statute of Limitation for fraud offenses, that\u0027s the term \u2018offenses,\u2019 committed during war."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.03,
                                "stop": 58.412,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "One of the questions presented in this case is whether the Wartime Suspension of Limitations Act applies solely to criminal charges or also to civil claims."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.412,
                                "stop": 62.548,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We hold that it applies only to criminal charges."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 62.548,
                                "stop": 76.869,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The term offenses generally refers to crimes not civil wrongs and that is the way the term is uniformly used in Title XVIII of the United States Code which is the title under which most federal crimes are grouped."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.869,
                                "stop": 84.542,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "For this reason it is telling that Congress codified the Wartime Suspension of Limitations Act in Title XVIII."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.542,
                                "stop": 90.145,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The wording of the statutory predecessors of the current statute is also revealing."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 90.145,
                                "stop": 94.903,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Those earlier measures referred to offenses now indictable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.903,
                                "stop": 109.781,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Since only crimes are indictable those earlier provisions clearly applied only to criminal charges and we are persuaded that the deletion of the words \u2018now indictable\u2019 was not meant to effect a radical change in meaning."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 109.781,
                                "stop": 114.963,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The second question in this case concerns the qui tam provision of the False Claims Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 114.963,
                                "stop": 122.79,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That provision bars the filing of an action while a related action is \u201cpending\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.79,
                                "stop": 129.866,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The question in this case is whether this bar persists after the earlier action is dismissed?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.866,
                                "stop": 134.286,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We hold that it does not."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 134.286,
                                "stop": 143.714,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We reject the argument that the first action remains pending in perpetuity that is simply not what the term pending means."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.714,
                                "stop": 154.33,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "For these and other reasons provided in our opinion the decision of the Fourth Circuit in this case is affirmed in part and reversed in part and the case is remanded for further proceedings consistent with this opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 154.33,
                                "stop": 156.792,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The decision is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
